desmoj.extensions.applicationDomains.production

Class PartsList

  • java.lang.Object
    • desmoj.core.simulator.NamedObject
      • desmoj.core.simulator.ModelComponent
        • desmoj.extensions.applicationDomains.production.PartsList

  • public class PartsList
extends ModelComponent
    A PartsList is a listing of all the different kinds of parts and the number (quantity) of them needed to produce a new part (or product). It is used in conjunction with a WorkStation in order to tell the work station how many and of which kind of parts should be assembled there. The user can instantiate a PartsList either by providing to arrays of the same length, one with all the different kinds of parts and one with the respective number of each different part, or by instantiating a PartsList with the number of different kinds of parts and then adding pairs of [kindOfPart, number of this kind of parts] using the addPart method.

      • PartsList

        public PartsList(Model ownerModel,
                 java.lang.String name,
                 int numberOfDifferentParts)
        Constructs a PartsList with enough space to store a number of different kinds of parts with the respective quantity needed of each kind. Use the method addPart to add a pair of [kind of part, quantity of that kind of part]. The PartsList leaves no messages in the trace.
        Parameters:
        ownerModel - desmoj.Model : The model this PartsList is associated to.
        name - java.lang.String : The name of this PartsList.
        numberOfDifferentParts - int : The number of different kinds of parts. Should not be zero or negative!

    • Method Detail

      • addPart

        public void addPart(java.lang.Class kindOfPart,
                    int numberOfParts)
        Adds a pair of [kind of part, quantity of that kind of part] to the PartsList. There can not be added more pairs than the PartsList can hold. To check how many pairs a PartList can hold use the method getNumberOfDiffParts().
        Parameters:
        kindOfPart - java.lang.Class : The kind of part as a Class object.
        numberOfParts - int : The number of that kind of part.

      • getIndexOfKind

        public int getIndexOfKind(java.lang.Class kind)
        Returns the index of the given kind of part ( java.lang.Class). The index is indicating the position in the array of kindOfParts. If the given kind of part is not found in this PartsList, undefinded (-1) will be returned.
        Parameters:
        kind - java.lang.Class : The kind of part given as an object of java.lang.Class.
        Returns:
        int : The index of the given kind of part ( java.lang.Class). That is the position in the array of kindOfParts. Or undefined (-1) if no such kind of part can be found in this PartsList.
